  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **PART 5 --- Decimal Feet ↔ Feet & Inches Conversion**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

Civil drawings use DECIMAL FEET. Construction crews use FEET & INCHES.
This table converts between the two. The engineer\'s scale reads in
decimal feet --- use this table to convert to feet and inches for field
layout.

**5.1 Decimal Feet to Inches Quick-Reference**

  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Decimal    **Inches**   **Decimal   **Inches**   **Decimal   **Inches**
  Feet**                    Feet**                   Feet**      
  ------------ ------------ ----------- ------------ ----------- ----------------
  **0.01\'**   1/8\"        0.26\'      3-1/8\"      0.51\'      6-1/8\"

  **0.02\'**   1/4\"        0.27\'      3-1/4\"      0.52\'      6-1/4\"

  **0.04\'**   1/2\"        0.29\'      3-1/2\"      0.54\'      6-1/2\"

  **0.06\'**   3/4\"        0.31\'      3-3/4\"      0.56\'      6-3/4\"

  **0.08\'**   1\"          0.33\'      4\"          0.58\'      7\"

  **0.10\'**   1-1/4\"      0.35\'      4-1/4\"      0.60\'      7-1/4\"

  **0.12\'**   1-1/2\"      0.37\'      4-1/2\"      0.63\'      7-1/2\"

  **0.14\'**   1-3/4\"      0.38\'      4-5/8\"      0.65\'      7-3/4\"

  **0.17\'**   2\"          0.40\'      4-3/4\"      0.67\'      8\"

  **0.19\'**   2-1/4\"      0.42\'      5\"          0.71\'      8-1/2\"

  **0.21\'**   2-1/2\"      0.44\'      5-1/4\"      0.75\'      9\"

  **0.23\'**   2-3/4\"      0.46\'      5-1/2\"      0.79\'      9-1/2\"

  **0.25\'**   3\"          0.48\'      5-3/4\"      0.83\'      10\"

  **---**      ---          0.50\'      6\"          0.88\'      10-1/2\"

  **---**      ---          ---         ---          0.92\'      11\"

  **---**      ---          ---         ---          0.96\'      11-1/2\"

  **---**      ---          ---         ---          1.00\'      12\" (1\'-0\")
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **★ PRO TIP:** FORMULA to convert: Decimal feet × 12 = inches. Example:
  0.75 ft × 12 = 9 inches. Or: Take the decimal portion only, multiply by
  12. For 5.75 feet: 5 feet + (0.75 × 12) = 5 feet 9 inches.

