                                       sides, H=height   cross-section, swale area

  **Circle**      A = π × r²           r=radius,         Cul-de-sac, circular
                                       π=3.14159         detention basin

  **Irregular     Divide into          ---               Odd-shaped parking lots,
  polygon**       triangles &                            irregular lots
                  rectangles, sum                        
                  areas                                  

  **Planimeter    Mechanical/digital   Trace perimeter   Fast area measurement of
  (tool)**        area trace           with device       any shape on paper
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**6.2 Converting Area to Different Units**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **From**     **To**       **Multiply   **Example**
                            By**         
  ------------ ------------ ------------ --------------------------------
  **Square     Square yards ÷ 9          900 SF ÷ 9 = 100 SY
  feet (SF)**  (SY)                      

  **Square     Square feet  × 9          100 SY × 9 = 900 SF
  yards (SY)** (SF)                      

  **Square     Acres (AC)   ÷ 43,560     87,120 SF ÷ 43,560 = 2.0 AC
  feet (SF)**                            

  **Acres      Square feet  × 43,560     2.5 AC × 43,560 = 108,900 SF
  (AC)**       (SF)                      

  **Acres      Square yards × 4,840      1 AC × 4,840 = 4,840 SY
  (AC)**       (SY)                      

  **Square     Square feet  × 10.764     100 m² × 10.764 = 1,076.4 SF
  meters       (SF)                      
  (m²)**                                 
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**6.3 Volume Calculation --- Prismatic Method**

For regular shapes (trenches, basins with uniform cross-section):

-   Volume (CF) = Cross-Section Area (SF) × Length (LF)

-   Volume (CY) = Volume (CF) ÷ 27

*Example: Trench 2.5 ft wide, 6 ft deep, 200 LF long. Volume = 2.5 × 6 ×
200 = 3,000 CF ÷ 27 = 111.1 CY*

**6.4 Volume Calculation --- Average End Area (AEA) Method**

For irregular shapes that change cross-section along their length
(roads, channels, grading areas):

-   Step 1: Calculate the cross-section area at Station 1 (A1, in SF)

-   Step 2: Calculate the cross-section area at Station 2 (A2, in SF)

-   Step 3: Volume (CF) = \[(A1 + A2) ÷ 2\] × Distance between stations
    (LF)

-   Step 4: Convert to CY: ÷ 27

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **★ PRO TIP:** Average End Area tends to OVERESTIMATE volume when
  cross-sections change rapidly. The Prismatoid Formula gives more
  accurate results but is rarely used in field estimating. AEA is the
  standard accepted method for earthwork bidding.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **PART 7 --- Digital Measuring Tools & Software**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**7.1 Bluebeam Revu (Industry Standard for PDF Take-Offs)**

Bluebeam Revu is the most widely used digital take-off tool in civil
construction. It works with PDF drawings.

-   Set the scale: use the Calibrate tool --- click on a known
    dimension, enter its value, and Bluebeam sets the scale
    automatically

-   Linear measurement: Measure tool → click start point → click end
    point → distance shown in real-world units

-   Area: Polygon or rectangle area tool --- click around the perimeter

-   Volume: Set a depth, multiply area by depth in the markups list

-   Count: Click each item (manholes, trees, etc.) --- auto-counts

-   Export: All measurements export to Excel for use in estimates

